## Spawn discipline (parents)

When calling MCP **`mission_control_spawn_agent`** on **plan-and-deliver** or other R&D spawn paths:

1. Set **`name`** to a short, topic-specific label (not generic placeholders like "Child agent" alone).
2. Include **`description`** (and optional spawn metadata the host maps to initial slot copy) so the Agents strip is readable before the child runs.
3. Follow **`missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`** § *Universal spawn preflight* — display metadata is part of spawn quality, not a post-hoc fix.
4. **Squad Leader** lanes update **dispatch** chrome only via **`mission_control_update_dispatch_display`** — see rule **9**; do not relabel child slots from the leader lane.

Spawn-heavy **`SKILL.md`** files and **`plan.mdc`** § *Spawn run-request display metadata* extend this baseline.

**Null-parent dispatch labels (cross-ref).** After PR 1–2 governance, **`plan and deliver`** defaults **`Parent: null`** — dispatch and lane titles must **not** imply a Hub roadmap topic or **`top_level_topic`** parent (for example “under topic X”). Use feature title, plan slug, or PR concern in **`name`** / **`dispatchTitle`**. Legacy Hub **`### Parent (Sedea Hub)`** openings may still appear until Mission Control host strip (Master Plan phase 2) — when present, echo the legacy parent in one acknowledgement line only; do **not** treat it as the long-term dispatch scope label. See **development-process.md** § *Root delivery plans vs legacy Hub parent intake* and rule **30** § *Root delivery plans only*.

