## Lane title prefix conventions (binding)

Every **`mission_control_spawn_agent`** **`name`** and child **`mission_control_update_lane_display`** **`title`** on R&D delivery lanes uses:

```text
{prefix}-{semantic title}
```

**Semantic title** — the topic-specific label spawners already derive (PRD title, feature planning title, phase scope, §1 single concern, PR slug). **Only** prepend the role prefix and a single hyphen — do not change how semantic titles are chosen.

| Skill role | Prefix | `[N]` when indexed | Typical spawner |
|------------|--------|--------------------|-----------------|
| **`author-prd`**, **`ad-hoc-prd`** | `PRD` | — | Squad Leader |
| **`master-planner`** | `MP` | — | Squad Leader |
| **`phase-planner`** | `PH{N}` | One-based **Delivery phases** list index (`parentIndex`) | **`new-plan`**, decomposition tree |
| **`coding-session`** | `PR{N}` | One-based **`### PR list`** index (`parentIndex`) | **`pr-plan`** §5d, planning child lanes |
| **`pre-pr-review`** | `Pre-PR Review` | — | **`coding-session`** |

**Examples:** `PRD-Checkout auth`, `MP-Notifications`, `PH2-Payments phase`, `PR1-Add webhook`, `Pre-PR Review-Order API`

**Max length:** Rule **9** caps **`title`** at **64** characters — truncate the semantic title if needed; **never** shorten the role prefix.

**Child refresh:** When spawn labels are stale, children refresh **own** slot via **`mission_control_update_lane_display`** using the same `{prefix}-{semantic title}` shape.

Operator checklist: **`missions/plan-and-deliver/skills/README.md`** § *Lane title prefix (spawn `name`)*.

