## Checkpoint step continuation (binding)

This file is the **R&D Mission Control display-metadata spawn / refresh / Squad Leader chrome contract**, not a mission protocol with executable ship steps. Under **`trustLevel: checkpoint`**, turn-end modal UX for display-update failures and ownership ambiguity uses **AskQuestion** / **`mission_control_present_structured_choice`** per sedea rules **2** / **1** and rule **9**; happy-path spawn labels, prefix application, and own-slot refresh **auto-advance**. **Do not** add literal `USER_CHECKPOINT` markers here for happy-path spawn `name` / `description`, `{prefix}-{semantic title}` application, or own-slot MCP refresh when labels are clearly stale — that would fight skill auto-advance.

| Surface | Designation | Owner |
|---------|-------------|--------|
| Spawn with topic-specific `name` + `description` when scope is clear | **auto-advance** | This § *Spawn discipline (parents)* |
| Apply `{prefix}-{semantic title}` on spawn / child refresh when role + index clear | **auto-advance** | This § *Lane title prefix conventions* |
| Child refreshes **own** stale slot via `mission_control_update_lane_display` | **auto-advance** | This § *Child lane — refresh own slot* |
| Skip lane MCP when spawn labels already match skill scope | **auto-advance** | This § *Child lane — refresh own slot* step 3 |
| Squad Leader updates dispatch chrome when dispatch scope is clear | **auto-advance** | This § *Squad Leader — dispatch chrome only* |
| Stale tab recovery when MCP fails or wrong lane owns the update | **checkpoint** | This § *Stale tab title recovery* step 4 — structured choice once; **forbidden** prose-only rename asks |
| Asking the developer to rename tabs in the UI as a substitute for MCP | **checkpoint** | This § *Child lane* / *Squad Leader* forbidden rows — modal or correct-owner MCP; never idle *rename the tab* handoff |
| Turn completion after a display-metadata decision in chat | **baseline-governs** (reference) | Rules **1**–**2**; pointer in Related below |

**Forbidden in this file:** prescribing prose *tell me when* / *come back when* / *I'll wait* / *over to you* / *ask how to proceed* / *rename the tab and tell me* as the primary wait surface for stale labels, MCP failure, or ownership-unsure stops; duplicating rule-9 / rule-2 AskQuestion option tables; `USER_CHECKPOINT` tokens for happy-path spawn labels, prefix application, or own-slot refresh.

**Related:** Checkpoint step-table template — [`.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/pr-step-table-template.md`](.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/pr-step-table-template.md). Marker syntax — [`.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/user-checkpoint-marker-syntax.md`](.sedea/centers/sedea/docs/user-checkpoint-marker-syntax.md).

